Three suspected armed robbery suspects alleged to have been terrorising motorists along Odogbolu/ ijebu ode expressway have been arrested by men of the Ogun state police command. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Deputy Superintendent of Police,DSP, Abimbola Oyeyemi, who is the state’s Police Public Relations Officer disclosed this in a statement made available to Daily Independent. He said the suspects were arrested when policemen attached to Odogbolu division who were on patrol of the highway sighted them at about 6 am placing themselves in an ambush manner along the express road. On seeing the policemen, the three of them took to their heels but they were chased and apprehended. Oyeyemi gave names of the arrested suspects as Johnson Afokolu, victor Michael and Jacob Usang. “On interrogation, they confessed being responsible for most of the robbery cases in the area adding that other members of their gang always joined them on special operations. “Recovered from them are; one toy gun, six torch lights,  military face cap, dried weeds suspected to be Indian hemp, knife, assorted clothes and three different types of hand set. Meanwhile, Oyeyemi said, the Commissioner of Police, CP, Bashir Makama has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspects to the state’s Special Anti-Robbery Squad for discreet investigation. He also ordered a massive manhunt for the remaining members of the gang in order to ensure sanity along the express road.